entries.femaleVariant: Shame, feel bad for her.
How you like that bombshell I promised?
Well, can put a check mark next to Hellman's name. Now we gotta--
Gotta admit, corpocunt's got a knack for drama.
Fuck!
Fuck!
No, third trimester cramping.
Ha ha ha, joke away, but you look pretty spent.
entries.maleVariant: Hah, you sure? Can't be that bad if you're makin' light.

entries.femaleVariant: Ugh. 'Course it's the damn chip. My Silverhandosis is clearly incubating…
entries.maleVariant: Ugh. Of course it's the damn chip. My Silverhandosis is clearly incubating…

entries.femaleVariant: That a pointed finger I hear in your voice?
No, it's you, you asshole! Killin' me little by little every damn day…
"Little by little" is not my style. It's the chip, it's Arasaka.
[Stand] Third trimester cramping.
[Stand] Of course it's the chip.
Fuck…!
That was your ticker. Sit and rest. Don't need you flatlinin' while we got a job to do.
[Stand] It's you, you bastard!
Blah blah blah, fuck Arasaka, blah blah, smash Mikoshi.
You really are turnin' into me.
[Don't smoke] Not good, you're a prick.
[Smoke] Prolly not wrong.
Can't say I'm excited 'cause you're a manipulator, an egotist, and a cynic... Every time you open your mouth you gotta bury someone.
entries.maleVariant: Can't say I'm excited cuz you're a manipulator, an egotist, and a cynic... Every time you open your mouth you gotta bury someone.

entries.femaleVariant: Ugh. Might be right.
We're bickering like a shriveled old married couple.
entries.maleVariant: We're bickering like a couple of geezers on a park bench.

entries.femaleVariant: But I don't even like you.
That the biochip?
Don't even know where I'm going.
Siddown, goddammit…
Y'know, we get along as the need arises. Maybe it's time you started trustin' me more.
You can be a charming guy – just make the effort, charisma flows.
Every cell of my being dislikes you... How can I trust you?
Got no idea where I'm goin'…
Problem is you think the ends justify the means.
It's time we let up, let a little trust take hold.
Do I gotta remind you how this came about?
Don't, c'mon...
Honestly can't fathom how you got so many people to bend over backwards for you.
It was Mikoshi I was after, wanted to destroy it. Gave 'Saka ample time to clear the building.
You knew countless people would die. Don't kid yourself.
The problem's the madman in my head.
We deserve each other.
No, the maniac in my head's the problem.
Got a point. Guess we make quite the duo.
You're unpredictable – that's my point.
Whatever, won't argue. All I'm sayin' is you're unpredictable.
Hah. Maniac in the head of a hypocrite.
No, we're not the same. What I did in 'Saka Tower... no doubts, no regrets.
Might fool someone else with that, but I call horseshit.
What do you know.
You pot, me kettle. Remember where you used to be, then think what you've done lately.
Mikoshi felt... I dunno, like sleep? Lacked awareness, had no sense of passing time, didn't mark it.
Did what they wanted to me. I just remember… cold, a black void, fear. Or-- or was that your death?
Guess I understand why you hate Mikoshi.
It's all so fucked up…
[Stand] Don't wanna hear it.
Got what you deserved.
[Stand] Let's get goin'.
Well, think I get why you detest the place.
Let's move, get back to work.
Shouldn't exist. Of all the destruction and pain corps wreak 'round the world, what happens at Mikoshi is worst.
Know why?
Eternity – it lasts forever.
You're denied the right to die.
They can change you into somebody else.
They experiment on the human psyche.
I dunno.
'Cause you're trapped there forever, it's eternal.
They strip you of your right to die.
They can change who you are. Turn you into someone else without you even knowin' it.
They're fuckin' around with the human mind, consciousness.
Honestly? Not sure.
The chosen and anointed die young. But you knew how it'd end.
You deserved to die.
Death? Sure. Vile prison – maybe.
But Mikoshi is so much worse. Any idea why?
No, nothing's eternal. And for the psyches in Mikoshi, no such thing as the passage of time.
No different than bein' kept alive on a respirator. That ain't the worst bit.
Yep... Goddamn right.
Corps've already taken the world for their own, now they're comin' for us.
Worst thing's when they switch up your identity and you never even know you've become someone else.
Corps've already taken the world for their own, now they're comin' for us.
Doin' the same to me, you know. Erasing my identity.
[Stand] Enough. Let's go.
Realize what you're doin' to me is what Arasaka's doin' at Mikoshi?
Yeah, I know... That's why I'm gonna fix it.
Take lives aplenty yourself. See scale as a problem?
Oh, right, forgot you're the gentle type, no killin'.
Problem is, you let loads of others do loads of killing for you.
Path clear, see where you're goin'?
Let's not get wound up – you're not yourself.
Got no idea what's happening to me.
[Stand] Can't stand you. I'm outta here.
That's it, had enough Johnny today.
Dunno what's happening to me.
The old V's gonna be a faded memory soon.
Got shit to take care of, so you pop back in your box, genie.
Fuck you, V.
Dunno where I'm going.
[Stand] Need to get our shit together.
Not any different than bein' a pharm corp's lab rat. Nah, it's somethin' else.
Lemme tell ya.
Who?
Was just thinkin' that...
Alt? No way you'd find her on your o-own…
entries.maleVariant: Heh, Alt? Heh, no way you'd find-- find 'er on your own…

entries.femaleVariant: Ngh, what's this?
Agh, what the--?
Now she'll try to wrap you 'round her--
Hey, w-what's happenin'...?
Mikoshi – why'd Arasaka even build it?
Why'd Arasaka build that place?
If I could only see inside Saburo's head…
Ha ha...
People can be bought, brainwashed, but it's only in Mikoshi that you can peer inside a soul, pick it apart... reprogram it.
Then I remember that nuke you detonated downtown without a second thought and no hint of later remorse.
Be a living legend – that's all I wanted. Feels like I'm barely survivin'.
Maybe.
Yeah... maybe.
Bullshit. Nothing dignifying in suffering, death... Not how legends are born.
Bullshit.
Test of a person's true value? Death – facing it, staring it down. You still got a chance to be somebody.
What was it like? When you died?
Was on top of the world. Failure – not an option, not a thought... till it happened. Death feels real now, it's only now I know it.
[Stand] Let's go.
Now? Had half a century to come to terms.
They've amassed quite a collection. Scary talented 'runners, soulkilled, packed away. Probably using them, now, probably controlling 'em.
So, ruling hearts and minds – that's what it's about. The usual.
entries.maleVariant: So, rulin' hearts and minds – that's what it's about. The usual.

entries.femaleVariant: Corps've always tried to shackle people one way or another. Saburo's ambition is greater – he's out to control humanity.
Let's do.
Really don't understand what people saw in you.
[Stand] Let's delta.
When you died – what was it like?
